PSXApplication.name: sys_psxContentEditorCataloger
PSXApplication.description: This application is used to provide catalogs of content editor components, such as content editor controls. One consumer of these catalogs is the E2Designer via the CatalogContentEditor* classes and the ApplicationRequestor.

PSXDataSet.name: Dataset771
PSXDataSet.description: Catalogs the choice sets (name of set and entries) available in RXLOOKUP. No parameters are needed.

PSXDataSet.name: getContentTypes
PSXDataSet.description: Provides a catalog of all the content types registered in the CONTENTTYPES table. An optional parameter "contenttypeid" may be provided to restrict the catalog to only that CONTENTTYPEID. Returns an empty document if the query returns no rows.

PSXDataSet.name: updatecontenttype
PSXDataSet.description: Creates or updates content types in the CONTENTTYPES table, keyed by the parameter "contenttypeid".

PSXDataSet.name: Dataset21
PSXDataSet.description: Gets the content editor URL that is used for the specified sys_contenttypeid or sys_contentid by outer-joining the CONTENTTYPES and CONTENTSTATUS tables. Used by PSActionSetRequestHandler.

PSXDataSet.name: getControls
PSXDataSet.description: Loads the content editor control definition stylesheets (sys_templates.xsl and rx_templates.xsl) and extracts the control metadata. Result XML format is: <Controls> <psxctl:ControlMeta>...</psxctl:ControlMeta> ... </Controls>

PSXDataSelector.nativeStatement: SELECT CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID, CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPELABEL FROM CONTENTTYPES CONTENTTYPES WHERE CONTENTTYPES.HIDEFROMMENU <> 1 AND CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID IN (SELECT DISTINCT RXSLOTCONTENT.CONTENTTYPEID FROM RXSLOTCONTENT RXSLOTCONTENT WHERE SLOTID=:"PSXSingleParam/sys_slotid") ORDER BY CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPELABEL ASC

SELECT DISTINCT CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID, CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPELABEL FROM CONTENTTYPES, RXCONTENTTYPECOMMUNITY WHERE RXCONTENTTYPECOMMUNITY.COMMUNITYID IN (:"PSXSingleParam/sys_communities") AND CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPEID = RXCONTENTTYPECOMMUNITY.CONTENTTYPEID ORDER BY CONTENTTYPES.CONTENTTYPELABEL ASC

PSXDataSet.name: getCommunityContentTypes
PSXDataSet.description: Provides a catalog of all the content types registered for the user's login community. Returns an empty document if the query returns no rows.

PSXDataSet.name: getAllItemContentTypes
PSXDataSet.description: Provides a catalog of all the content types registered in the CONTENTTYPES table whose object type is 1. An optional parameter "contenttypeid" may be provided to restrict the catalog to only that CONTENTTYPEID. Returns an empty document if the query returns no rows.

PSXDataSet.name: WorkflowContentTypeCommunityLookup
PSXDataSet.description: Lookup for allowed workflow ids based on lists of content type and community ids.
